events.title: Manaslu Circuit Trek, Nepal Himalaya (5210m) - 16 Days
events.description: Trekking in Nepal Mt.Manslu ( 8163m eight highest mountain in the world and is one of the fourteen 8000‚Å∫ meter peaks. it dominates the Manaslu range bordering the Ganesh Himal range on the east and Annapurna to the west. Since the border with Tibet is a strategic location. The area is considered as restricted trekking destination where trek must be fully organized through a reputed trekking Agency. Like in other restricted trekking places, the permit is issued and regulated by the Immigration Department of Nepal. The area is relatively untouched by tourism but the numbers are exceeding dramatically the Manaslu circuit Trek start from a small village near the historic Gorkha (Gurkha) kingdom now a district of Nepal. We pass through lush hills and canyons dotted with enchanting villages on our way to Larkya la (5163m) one of the beautiful passes of the Himalaya. We drop down from Larky la to Marshayangdi valley, part of the Annapurna circuit and to the road which leads us back to Kathmandu. Since Annapurna circuit dying due to road construction, the Manaslu circuit is dramatically becoming one of the very popular trekking place in the Himalaya.
events.author: Our Club is registered on The British Mountaineering Council (BMC)
